r your body until your arms form a 90-degree angle at the elbow then return to the starting position.";i:11;s:53:"Your fingers should grip the front of the chair seat.";i:12;s:62:"Move your torso forward off the chair with your arms extended.";i:13;s:76:"Your buttocks should hover over the floor and your knees should be slightly.";i:14;s:75:"If you ever do lat shrugs you can hit lats pretty good from a dip position.";i:15;s:139:"Dips of course do more trischest but some people might have a little bit of that lat shrug motion in there as well when doing regular dips.";i:16;s:41:"Try to accentuate the lats a little more.";i:17;s:38:"How many chair dips should I do a day.";i:18;s:67:"You should try to do 10 to 15 repetitions of this exercise per set.";i:19;s:67:"Start off by doing two sets of bench dips in each of your workouts.";i:20;s:110:"Once you feel you can complete that with ease move on to three sets of 10 to 15 reps and then on to four sets.";i:21;s:46:"This should be challenging but not impossible.";i:22;s:99:"The triceps dip can be performed using a single chairbench or two of them for experienced athletes.";i:23;s:69:"Place your hands on the bench so that the fingers are facing forward.";i:24;s:108:"Now raise your legs and place them on the second bench of equal height thats placed three to four feet away.";i:25;s:53:"Are dips more shoulder-friendly than the bench press.";i:26;s:26:"This is a tricky question.";i:27;s:230:"While the bench press has the potential to cause many shoulder problems mainly due to bad technique and too much weight some people cant do dips but bench pain-free because the shoulder doesnt extend as far as it does during dips.";i:28;s:44:"To do a chair dip heres what you need to do.";i:29;s:116:"Sit on a chair with your feet firmly planted on the ground and your palms face down on the chair either side of you.";i:30;s:105:"Shift yourself forward until your whole body is off the chair but your arms are still pushing down on it.";i:31;s:118:"Parallel bar dips enable you to utilize your entire body weight thus providing higher resistance and a better workout.";i:32;s:131:"This method gives you the flexibility to zero-in on either your chest or triceps muscles just by positioning your body accordingly.";i:33;s:90:"See the latter section Difference Between Chest Dips and Tricep Dips for more information.";i:34;s:24:"Seated dips gym station.";i:35;s:172:"Seated Dip Data Region of the body Upper body Targeted musculature Triceps Training objective Strength Dimensions LxWxH 132 x 92 x 132 cm Weight 162 kg Software milon Care.";i:36;s:44:"Compare this product Remove from comparison.";i:37;s:141:"Performing Tricep Dips on One Chair Mount the single chair with your palms facing down and your hands pointing away from each other as shown.";i:38;s:141:"Bend your legs slightly at the knees with your feet extended away from the chair and start with your arms nearly straight in the up position.";i:39;s:49:"Dips can be done on a chair or on a weight bench.";i:40;s:66:"To do a dip sit and place your hands palms down next to your hips.";i:41;s:53:"Hang your fingers off the edge of the chair or bench.";i:42;s:55:"Straighten your arms and slide your hips off the chair.";i:43;s:86:"Inhale bend your arms and point your elbows behind you as you lower into the exercise.";i:44;s:32:"Exhale and straighten your arms.";i:45;s:46:"Use a dip bar for a more challenging exercise.";i:46;s:29:"To do the chair dip exercise.";i:47;s:38:"Place a sturdy chair in an open space.";i:48;s:66:"Sit down and wrap your fingers around the front edge of the chair.";i:49;s:66:"Slide your body forward until your buttocks is just off the chair.";i:50;s:36:"Start with your arms fully extended.";i:51;s:37:"Adjust your feet so your heels are a.";i:52;s:121:"Chair dips are a great alternative to regular dips if you want to increase arm core and lower back strength among others.";i:53;s:175:"As delicious as they may sound chair dips are not something to scoop up with potato chips on a lazy day but rather a variation of an exercise designed to work on your triceps.";i:54;s:79:"Chair dips are generally considered an easier exercise than regular dips which.";i:55;s:60:"Dips are an effective bodyweight triceps and chest exercise.";i:56;s:56:"They are not for beginners who lack upper body strength.";i:57;s:84:"Doing dips can help build grip strength bust plateaus and build serious muscle mass.";i:58;s:65:"They can be done at the gym or at home with some basic equipment.";i:59;s:67:"Dips are traditionally done using a machine parallel bars or rings.";i:60;s:106:"Chair dips are also called tricep dips because they work the tricep muscles on the back of the upper arms.";i:61;s:83:"Triceps is the muscle group that gives the pushing strength when executing the dip.";i:62;s:157:"Whether you are doing chest or triceps focused dips many of the targeted upper body muscle groups are the same focusing on the chest shoulders arms and back.";i:63;s:86:"The dip focuses on your pectorals or your triceps depending on the width of your grip.";i:64;s:65:"When using a shoulder-width grip you engage more of your triceps.";i:65;s:44:"A wider grip concentrates on your pectorals.";i:66;s:65:"Either way to do dips start by standing in between parallel bars.";i:67;s:42:"Two chairs back-to-back are commonly used.";i:68;s:104:"The keys to bringing the chest and lats into this exercise and differentiating it from triceps dips are.";i:69;s:49:"The slightly wider than shoulder width bar width.";i:70;s:54:"Moving the body slightly forward as you dip head down.";i:71;s:91:"Allowing your elbows to slightly flare out just slightly outside of your wrists as you dip.";i:72;s:21:"How to do chair dips.";i:73;s:77:"Sit on a chair and place your hands on it with your fingers facing the front.";i:74;s:99:"Extend your legs out in front of you at hip-distance apart with only your heels touching the floor.";i:75;s:24:"Chair Bench Tricep Dips.";i:76;s:83:"Sit on 